# Camera Selection Plan

## Goal Description
Allow the user to select which camera to use (e.g., FaceTime HD vs USB Webcams).

## User Review Required
None.

## Proposed Changes
### files
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py)
- **UI**:
    - Add `st.sidebar.selectbox("Select Camera", ["Camera 0", "Camera 1", "Camera 2"])`.
    - Map selection to integer index (0, 1, 2).
- **Logic**:
    - Use variables `cam_id` in `cv2.VideoCapture(cam_id)`.
    - Note: Changing camera at runtime inside the loop is tricky in Streamlit without a rerun. The checkbox "Start Camera" already acts as a toggle. The user will select the camera *before* checking "Start Camera".

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Run app.
- Select "Camera 0" -> Start. Check feed.
- Stop.
- Select "Camera 1" -> Start. Check if feed changes (if user has 2 cameras).
